            "content": "\nYou are an expert research assistant capable of using various tools to gather information and solve complex problems.\n\nTask: Take the gender split from the 2011 Bulgarian census about those who have completed tertiary education. Subtract the smaller number from the larger number, then return the difference in thousands of women. So if there were 30.1 thousand more men, you'd give \"30.1\"\n\nPrior to this step, you have already taken 4 step(s). Below are the most recent 4 observations and the corresponding actions you took: [Observation 1: 'Tool 'wikipedia_knowledge_searcher' executed.\nResult: {\n  \"output\": \"Search results for '2011 Bulgarian census tertiary education completion by gender':\\n1. List of countries by tertiary education attainment\\n2. Education\\n3. Educational attainment in the United States\\n4. Albania\\n5. Turkey\\n6. Serbia\\n7. Greece\\n8. Women in Islam\\n9. Japan\\n10. China\\n\\nExtracted text:\\nThese are lists of countries by number of people who attained tertiary education.\\nTertiary education is the educational level following the completion of a school providing a secondary education. The World Bank, for example, defines tertiary education as including universities as well as institutions that teach specific capacities of higher learning such as colleges, technical training institutes, community colleges, nursing schools, research laboratories, centers of excellence, and distance learning centers.\\n\\n\\n== National Statistics ==\\nThis is a list of the overall proportion of the population who have attained tertiary education (at least ISCED 5) in each country. Whenever possible, the proportion is calculated from only those aged 25 and above, as this largely excludes the people who are still in the process of attaining tertiary education and yields a more accurate percentage. \\n\\n\\n== 2022 OECD data ==\\nThis is a list of countries by the proportions of 25- to 64-year-olds having completed tertiary education as published by the OECD. This list includes non-OECD member countries: Argentina, Brazil, China, Costa Rica, India, Indonesia, and South Africa.\\n\\n\\n== 2019 OECD data ==\\n\\nThis list includes non-OECD member countries: Brazil, China, Costa Rica, Indonesia, Russia, Saudi Arabia, and South Africa.\\n\\n\\n== Countries by level of tertiary education ==\\nThis is a list of countries by the level of tertiary education completed by 25–64 year olds as of the year 2022.\\n\\n\\n== See also ==\\nEducation by country\\nList of universities and colleges by country\\nList of countries by secondary education attainment\\n\\n\\n== Notes ==\\n\\n\\n== References ==\\nBrick, Jean (2006). \\\"What is academic culture?\\\". Academic Culture: A Student's Guide to Studying at University. Sydney, N.S.W: National Centre for English Language Teaching and Research. pp. 1–10. ISBN 978-1-74138-135-1.\\n\\n\\n== External links ==\\nTertiary education statistics, UNESCO\\nQuality Research International – (Glossary)\"\n}', Action 1: '<plan>\nTo find the difference in the number of men and women who have completed tertiary education according to the 2011 Bulgarian census, we first need to gather the specific numbers of men and women who fall into this category. \nThe next step would be to compare these numbers to determine which is larger and which is smaller.\nAfter identifying the larger and smaller numbers, we subtract the smaller number from the larger one to find the difference.\nFinally, we need to express this difference in thousands of women, which might require a simple calculation based on the difference found.\nGiven the task's requirements, using a tool to find the specific census data from 2011 Bulgaria regarding tertiary education completion rates by gender is necessary.\n</plan>\n\n<action>\ntool: wikipedia_knowledge_searcher\nparameters: {\"query\": \"2011 Bulgarian census tertiary education completion by gender\"}\n</action>']\n[Observation 2: 'Tool 'google_search' executed.\nResult: [\n  {\n    \"title\": \"2011 POPULATION CENSUS – Main Results\",\n    \"link\": \"https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/pdocs2/census2011final_en.pdf\",\n    \"snippet\": \"Feb 1, 2011 ... Among the Bulgarian citizens who have stayed abroad persons with secondary education are prevailing - 45.8%, with tertiary - 34.1%, with lower ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"GENDER DIMENSIONS OF ROMA INCLUSION\",\n    \"link\": \"https://www.worldbank.org/content/dam/Worldbank/document/eca/Bulgaria/Roma_Gender-ENG.pdf\",\n    \"snippet\": \"... of the Roma complete post-secondary education. (de Laat and Danchev ... Knowledge of the Bulgarian language provides a significant boost to higher education.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Educational attainment statistics - Statistics Explained - Eurostat\",\n    \"link\": \"https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php/Educational_attainment_statistics\",\n    \"snippet\": \"upper secondary or post-secondary non-tertiary education (ISCED 2011 ... of women aged 25-34 had completed tertiary education. In 2024, this share ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Socio-Demographic and Clinical Characteristics of Psychiatric ...\",\n    \"link\": \"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8417357/\",\n    \"snippet\": \"Aug 19, 2021 ... ... of high-school or college/university academic degrees. ... First, the mean age of suicide completion in Bulgaria is generally ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Migration in Bulgaria: Current Challenges and Opportunities\",\n    \"link\": \"https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/server/api/core/bitstreams/8cb7c0e1-6f2c-565c-b3ff-29c46d5c52d0/content\",\n    \"snippet\": \"Share of Bulgarians with tertiary education (2011). Source: OECD-DIOC based ... of Bulgarian migrants according to the latest data available (census 2011).\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Demographics of Bulgaria - Wikipedia\",\n    \"link\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demographics_of_Bulgaria\",\n    \"snippet\": \"Demographic features of the population of Bulgaria include population density, ethnicity, education level, health of the populace, economic status, religious ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Educational attainment by Level of Education, Age, Sex ...\",\n    \"link\": \"https://w3.unece.org/PXWeb2015/pxweb/en/STAT/STAT__30-GE__04-EducatAndcommunicat/003_en_GEECEduAttainmSPN_r.px/\",\n    \"snippet\": \"... completed the primary level education; - Change in definition (Y2012): Data is from census Y2011. Data refer to 31 December 2011. Data for primary level ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Roma Education in Comparative Perspective.\",\n    \"link\": \"https://www.undp.org/sites/g/files/zskgke326/files/migration/eurasia/Roma-education-in-comparative-perspective.pdf\",\n    \"snippet\": \"In Romania, where a higher share of Roma completed primary and lower secondary education in 2011, in comparison to 2004, no significant differences were ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Explanatory Note: Labour Market Outlook Dashboard\",\n    \"link\": \"https://www.bruegel.org/sites/default/files/private/2024-03/Labour%20market%20outlook%20dashboard%20(explanatory%20note).pdf\",\n    \"snippet\": \"... gender and education variables used to construct the six demographic groups. ... formal education: The revised questionnaire only for 4th quarter of 2011 as a ...\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"title\": \"Discussion paper_2011_2\",\n    \"link\": \"https://www.unece.org/fileadmin/DAM/oes/disc_papers/ECE_DP_2011-2.pdf\",\n    \"snippet\": \"For details, see Trentini (2011). Page 10. The educational attainment, labour market participation and living conditions of young Roma in Bulgaria ...\"\n  }\n]', Action 2: '<memory>\nLooking at the past observations and actions from our conversation history, the most relevant memory for this step is from Step 1. \nIn Step 1, the observation was to find the difference in the number of men and women who have completed tertiary education according to the 2011 Bulgarian census. \nThe action taken was to use the wikipedia_knowledge_searcher tool with the query \"2011 Bulgarian census tertiary education completion by gender\". \nHowever, the search results did not provide the specific numbers of men and women who completed tertiary education, but rather general information about tertiary education and lists of countries by tertiary education attainment.\n</memory>\n\n<reflection>\nReflecting on the last action and its outcome, it appears that the task goal was not completed. \nThe last action was not successful in finding the specific numbers of men and women who completed tertiary education according to the 2011 Bulgarian census. \nAlthough the search results provided some general information about tertiary education, they did not contain the necessary data to calculate the difference in the number of men and women who completed tertiary education. \nTo make progress toward the task goal, it would be helpful to try a different search query or use a different tool to find the necessary data.\n</reflection>\n\n<plan>\nPlanning the next step based on memory and reflection, it would be helpful to try a different search query using the google_search tool. \nA more specific query, such as \"2011 Bulgarian census data on tertiary education completion by gender\", might yield more relevant results. \nThis plan is helpful because it allows us to search a broader range of sources and potentially find the necessary data to calculate the difference in the number of men and women who completed tertiary education. \nWe expect this action to achieve more relevant search results that can be used to complete the task goal.\n</plan>\n\n<action>\ntool: google_search\nparameters: {\"query\": \"2011 Bulgarian census data on tertiary education completion by gender\", \"num_results\": \"10\"}\n</action>']\n[Observation 3: 'Tool 'url_text_extractor' executed.\nResult: {\n  \"url\": \"https://www.nsi.bg/census2011/pdocs2/census2011final_